cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on comparing different interaction techniques for smart glasses.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as smart glasses involve capturing and processing visual information.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper discusses the display and manipulation of graphical elements on smart glasses.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could be relevant as the paper involves selecting targets in a digital environment.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be relevant as smart glasses involve the integration of multiple forms of media (e.g. visual, audio).
